Lest We Forget: The Best Of (Album)
Lest We Forget: The Best Of is the first greatest hits album by Marilyn Manson. 
A new song was recorded to promote the album, a cover of Depeche Mode's "Personal Jesus".
The album was released at the end of September 2004.
The album cover is one of Marilyn Manson's watercolor paintings, titled "Experience is The Mistress of Fools". 
The deluxe edition includes a DVD containing most of the band's music videos. 
The album was certified Gold in USA and was supported with the band's Against All Gods Tour.
Manson initially called Lest We Forget the band's "farewell album" because the band would become a solo career for him
However, Marilyn Manson has since recorded additional studio albums as a band.
